Description: Two links of a gold chain made of thin wires of square cross-section, of a doubled twisted eight-shaped with a small gold ring around the central narrowest part of each link.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, From the denuded surface of the site or the neighbourhood ?
Curator's comments: One of the gold "pieces of chain" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 76 § 73, "piece of gold chain with a band round each link", ibid., p. 110 pl. xli, 24.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 76 § 73, p. 110, pl. xli, 24)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.83, p.84, p.186, pl.28)
